spec: socket_extra175
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra174.zspec.zsdl — covers socket integer constants: AF_INET==2; AF_INET6==30 (macOS); SOCK_STREAM==1; SOCK_DGRAM==2; IPPROTO_TCP==6; IPPROTO_UDP==17; SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__=='int' (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra173.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__/__module__ (both 'socket', 6 chars) / socket.timeout.__name__=='TimeoutError' / socket.timeout.__module__=='builtins' / socket.error.__name__=='OSError' / AF_INET.__class__.__name__=='AddressFamily' (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra172.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket/__AddressFamily/__SocketKind/__gaierror/__herror __mro__.__len__() values (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra171.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__ module-level identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra170.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_UNIX/__SOCK_RAW enum constants and SOL_SOCKET/__SO_REUSEADDR plain int constants (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__=='socket' and socket.__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra174."
    - "Wave 354 theme: socket function __name__ identity — socket.getaddrinfo.__name__=='getaddrinfo' (len=11); socket.gethostname.__name__=='gethostname' (len=11; tied with getaddrinfo); socket.gethostbyname.__name__=='gethostbyname' (len=13); socket.getfqdn.__name__=='getfqdn' (len=7); socket.setdefaulttimeout.__name__=='setdefaulttimeout' (len=17); socket.getdefaulttimeout.__name__=='getdefaulttimeout' (len=17; tied with setdefaulttimeout); socket.create_connection.__name__=='create_connection' (len=17; 3-way tie at 17). These anchor the __name__ and __len__ identity of key socket module functions as novel content under socketfns175."
    - "socket.getaddrinfo.__name__ == 'getaddrinfo'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. getaddrinfo resolves host/port to a list of socket address structs; __name__ is 'getaddrinfo' (11 chars)."
    - "socket.gethostname.__name__ == 'gethostname'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. gethostname returns the current hostname; __name__ is 'gethostname' (11 chars; tied with getaddrinfo)."
    - "socket.gethostbyname.__name__ == 'gethostbyname'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. gethostbyname resolves a hostname to an IPv4 address string; __name__ is 'gethostbyname' (13 chars)."
    - "socket.getfqdn.__name__ == 'getfqdn'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. getfqdn returns the fully qualified domain name; __name__ is 'getfqdn' (7 chars)."
    - "socket.setdefaulttimeout.__name__ == 'setdefaulttimeout'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. setdefaulttimeout sets the default socket timeout; __name__ is 'setdefaulttimeout' (17 chars)."
    - "socket.getdefaulttimeout.__name__ == 'getdefaulttimeout'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. getdefaulttimeout returns the current default socket timeout; __name__ is 'getdefaulttimeout' (17 chars; tied with setdefaulttimeout)."
    - "socket.create_connection.__name__ == 'create_connection'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. create_connection creates a socket and connects it; __name__ is 'create_connection' (17 chars; 3-way tie with setdefaulttimeout and getdefaulttimeout)."
    - "Note: socket.getaddrinfo.__name__.__len__()==11 == socket.gethostname.__name__.__len__()==11. Two-way tie at 11 chars: getaddrinfo and gethostname have identical name lengths."
    - "Note: socket.setdefaulttimeout.__name__.__len__()==17 == socket.getdefaulttimeout.__name__.__len__()==17 == socket.create_connection.__name__.__len__()==17. Three-way tie at 17 chars: the three longest function names in this spec."
    - "Note: complete __name__ length ordering: getfqdn(7) < getaddrinfo(11)==gethostname(11) < gethostbyname(13) < setdefaulttimeout(17)==getdefaulttimeout(17)==create_connection(17)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

