invariant socket_extra175.getaddrinfo_name_getaddrinfo:
  description: "socket.getaddrinfo.__name__.__eq__('getaddrinfo') == True — 'getaddrinfo' (11 chars; socket.getaddrinfo is the POSIX-standard address resolution function (getaddrinfo(3)); it translates a host name (e.g. 'www.example.com') and service name (e.g. 'http' or '80') into a list of 5-tuples (family, type, proto, canonname, sockaddr) suitable for creating and connecting a socket; getaddrinfo is the modern replacement for the deprecated gethostbyname — it supports both IPv4 and IPv6; __name__=='getaddrinfo' (11 chars: the 'get' prefix + 'addrinfo'); socket.getaddrinfo.__name__(11) == socket.gethostname.__name__.__len__()==11: two-way tie at 11 chars; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors getaddrinfo.__name__ under socketfns175; first socketfns175 standalone for getaddrinfo.__name__.__eq__('getaddrinfo')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: getaddrinfo.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["getaddrinfo"]
  expected: true

