  description: "socket.gethostname.__name__.__eq__('gethostname') == True — 'gethostname' (11 chars; socket.gethostname is a wrapper around the POSIX gethostname(2) system call; it returns the hostname of the machine as a string — typically the local machine's short hostname configured in the OS; gethostname is a thin wrapper: it takes no arguments and returns a str; __name__=='gethostname' (11 chars: 'get' + 'hostname'); gethostname.__name__(11) == getaddrinfo.__name__.__len__()==11: two-way name-length tie; 'gethostname' and 'getaddrinfo' both start with 'get' and both end in 'a' — coincidental shared suffix; gethostname(11) < gethostbyname(13) by 2: 'gethostbyname' is 2 chars longer than 'gethostname' due to the 'by' infix; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors gethostname.__name__ under socketfns175; first socketfns175 standalone for gethostname.__name__.__eq__('gethostname')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
