invariant socket_extra175.setdefaulttimeout_name:
  description: "socket.setdefaulttimeout.__name__.__eq__('setdefaulttimeout') == True — 'setdefaulttimeout' (17 chars; socket.setdefaulttimeout(timeout) sets the default timeout in seconds for blocking socket operations on new socket objects; if timeout is None, sockets are created in blocking mode with no timeout; if timeout is 0, sockets are created in non-blocking mode; setdefaulttimeout affects only newly created sockets; __name__=='setdefaulttimeout' (17 chars: 'set' + 'default' + 'timeout'); setdefaulttimeout.__name__(17) == getdefaulttimeout.__name__(17) == create_connection.__name__(17): 3-way tie at 17 chars — the longest function names in this spec; setdefaulttimeout(17) > gethostbyname(13) by 4; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors setdefaulttimeout.__name__ under socketfns175; first socketfns175 standalone for setdefaulttimeout.__name__.__eq__('setdefaulttimeout')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: setdefaulttimeout.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["setdefaulttimeout"]
  expected: true

