invariant socket_extra175.getdefaulttimeout_name:
  description: "socket.getdefaulttimeout.__name__.__eq__('getdefaulttimeout') == True — 'getdefaulttimeout' (17 chars; socket.getdefaulttimeout() returns the current default timeout value in seconds for new socket objects, as set by setdefaulttimeout(); returns None if no default timeout has been set (sockets are blocking); returns a float (or 0.0 for non-blocking) if a timeout is set; __name__=='getdefaulttimeout' (17 chars: 'get' + 'default' + 'timeout'); getdefaulttimeout.__name__(17) == setdefaulttimeout.__name__(17): the getter and setter are symmetric in name length; 'getdefaulttimeout' and 'setdefaulttimeout' differ only in the first 3 chars: 'get' vs 'set'; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors getdefaulttimeout.__name__ under socketfns175; first socketfns175 standalone for getdefaulttimeout.__name__.__eq__('getdefaulttimeout')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
