invariant socket_extra175.create_connection_name:
  description: "socket.create_connection.__name__.__eq__('create_connection') == True — 'create_connection' (17 chars; socket.create_connection(address, timeout, source_address) is a convenience function that creates a TCP socket connected to the given (host, port) address tuple; it internally calls getaddrinfo, creates the appropriate socket, and calls connect() — handling both IPv4 and IPv6 transparently; create_connection is widely used in higher-level networking libraries; __name__=='create_connection' (17 chars: 'create' + '_' + 'connection'); create_connection.__name__(17) == setdefaulttimeout.__name__(17) == getdefaulttimeout.__name__(17): 3-way tie at 17 chars; 'create_connection' uses an underscore separator (snake_case) while 'setdefaulttimeout' and 'getdefaulttimeout' use no separator (one merged word) — different naming conventions within the same module; complete name-length ordering in spec: getfqdn(7) < getaddrinfo(11)==gethostname(11) < gethostbyname(13) < setdefaulttimeout(17)==getdefaulttimeout(17)==create_connection(17); novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors create_connection.__name__ under socketfns175; first socketfns175 standalone for create_connection.__name__.__eq__('create_connection')"
  category: identity
